{{Quote|Before the dawn of the second sun, there dwelt beneath the oceans a magical god-beast. He was called Protas, for he was the first and only of his kind: a god, and a beast, and the ruler of all animals beneath the surface.|From "'''The Tale of the Aiwha Pod'''"|<ref name="Tale">{{StoryCite|story=The Tale of the Aiwha Pod (short story)|book=Star Wars: Republic Commando: Prima Official Game Guide}}</ref>}}
"'''The Tale of the Aiwha Pod'''" is a one-page [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] [[List of short stories|short story]] written by [[Ryan Kaufman (real person)|Ryan Kaufman]]. It was published in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando: Prima Official Game Guide]]'', which was released on [[March 8]], [[2005]]. The story is the [[The Tale of the Aiwha Pod|tale]] of a [[Kaminoan/Legends|Kaminoan]] [[Deity/Legends|deity]], [[Protas]], as [[Translator/Legends|translated]] by [[Ryan Kaufman]] from the [[Kaminoan (language)/Legends|Kaminoan]] [[Language/Legends|language]] to [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]]. Protas' rule of the [[Ocean/Legends|seas]] of [[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]] is challenged first by a great titan named [[Melkorr]], then by an army of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[kikla]]. [[Death/Legends|Killing]] the challengers, Protas becomes arrogant and prevents an [[Aiwha/Legends|aiwha]] [[Pod (social group)|pod]] from migrating south. Realizing they must attack or die, the [[Unidentified aiwha pod|aiwha pod]] attacks and defeats Protas in a [[Blood/Legends|bloody]] battle, in part due to [[Unidentified aiwha|one aiwha]] sacrificing itself.

The story opens with the line "Translated from the Kaminoan by Ryan Kaufman" to credit the real-life author, thus placing Kaufman in the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe. This makes Kaufman the only real-life person to have a character with the same name in ''Star Wars'' lore.

==Plot summary==
{{Quote|You cannot pass. Go back to the north seas and freeze.''"<br />"''Why, Master Protas?''"<br />"''Because it pleases me.|Protas and the aiwha pod, "The Tale of the Aiwha Pod"|<ref name="Tale" />}}
"The Tale of the Aiwha Pod" recounts the [[Kaminoan/Legends|Kaminoan]] [[The Tale of the Aiwha Pod|tale]] of the [[Deity/Legends|god-beast]] [[Protas]] and how he was defeated by a pod of [[Aiwha/Legends|aiwha]], as [[Translator/Legends|translated]] by [[Ryan Kaufman]] from the [[Kaminoan (language)/Legends|Kaminoan]] [[Language/Legends|language]] into [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]]. The story explains that before the dawn of the second [[Star/Legends|sun]], the [[Magic/Legends|mystical]] being Protas rules the [[Ocean/Legends|oceans]] of [[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]]. His claim as the most powerful in the [[Water/Legends|seas]] is challenged, first by [[Melkorr]], a massive titan from the deep. With a jaw full of sharp [[Tooth/Legends|teeth]] and large, pointed fins, Melkorr meets Protas on the underwater ridge of [[Thalina]]. Trying to use his size and power to overwhelm Protas, Melkorr [[Battle of Thalina|battles]] for six days and nights. However, the god-beast uses his agility and speed to evade the titan's attacks, tiring Melkorr. Taking advantage of his opponent's exhaustion, Protas deals a [[Death/Legends|killing]] blow, leaving the seas [[Blood/Legends|bloodied]] and feeding [[Fish/Legends|fish]] for an [[Time/Legends|eon]].<ref name="aiwha">{{StoryCite|story=The Tale of the Aiwha Pod (short story)|book=Star Wars: Republic Commando: Prima Official Game Guide}}</ref>

Protas is later challenged by an army of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[kikla]], who believed that their large numbers would make up for their comparatively small size and would be able to overwhelm the god-beast. Meeting Protas in the deep waters of the [[Ancient Trench]], they [[Battle of the Ancient Trench|fight]] for a [[Standard month/Legends|month]]. Though legion in number, the kikla are divided in [[Brain/Legends|mind]] and argue amongst themselves, leaving only small wounds on the god-beast. In comparison, Protas is of a single mind and slowly [[Foodstuff/Legends|eats]] the kikla to maintain strength, and at the new [[Moon/Legends|moon]], the last kikla is eaten and Protas is again victorious.<ref name="aiwha" />

Becoming old and arrogant in his victories and power, Protas eventually comes across a [[Unidentified aiwha pod|pod]] of [[Aiwha/Legends|aiwha]], who are swimming south to avoid the [[Temperature/Legends|cold]] [[Winter/Legends|winter]]. Blocking their path, Protas refuses to let them continue and instructs the aiwha to return north, simply for his amusement. Knowing they will die if they turn back, the aiwha [[Destruction of Protas|attack]] without warning, since they do not desire glory or fame. The aiwha combine the swarming tactics of the kikla with the powerful attacks of Melkorr but cannot deal a killing blow through Protas' thick skin.<ref name="aiwha" />

[[Unidentified aiwha|One aiwha]], noticing Protas has briefly exposed the soft flesh of his throat, clamps onto the god-beast in a sacrificial attempt to defeat him. Realizing his dire position, Protas attempts to dislodge the aiwha by smashing it with his fins, but it will not let go, even in death. This allows the rest of the aiwha to deal a final blow, ending the god-beast's life. The story is told as an explanation of why the aiwha rule the oceans and are given respect by all the creatures of Kamino, great and small, as they defeated Protas and brought peace to the seas.<ref name="aiwha" />

==Development==
{{Quote|Translated from the Kaminoan by Ryan Kaufman|Opening line of "The Tale of the Aiwha Pod"|<ref name="Tale" />}}
"The Tale of the Aiwha Pod" is a one-page [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] [[List of short stories|short story]] published by [[Prima Games]] in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando: Prima Official Game Guide]]'',<ref name="RCPG" /> which was released [[March 8]], [[2005]].<ref name="Amazon" /> It was written by [[Ryan Kaufman (real person)|Ryan Kaufman]] and edited by [[Rebecca Chastain]].<ref name="RCPG" /> The story's opening line notes that the tale is presented as a translation into Basic by Kaufman, to credit him specifically for the short story.<ref name="aiwha" /> This earns "The Tale of the Aiwha Pod" the unique distinction as the only ''[[Star Wars]]'' tale featuring a character&mdash;[[Ryan Kaufman]]&mdash;with a name that is identical to its real-world counterpart.

